7, 2010}}</ref> <ref>{{cite news|title=Randolph joins Slovenia for EuroBasket|url=http://www.eurohoops.net/en/national-teams/469359/randolph-joins-slovenia-eurobasket/|accessdate=June 23, 2017|work=Eurohoops.net|date=June 23, 2017}}</ref>}}\n{{Cnote|c|Roy Hibbert was born in the United States to a [[Jamaica]]n father and a [[Trinidad and Tobago|Trinidadian]] mother. He had represented the United States internationally at youth level in 2007.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-dyn/content/story/2007/12/21/ST2007122102522.html|title=Fast Friends, Big Rivals|first=Camille|last=Powell|date=December 22, 2007|work=The Washington Post|publisher=The Washington Post|accessdate=August 15, 2011}}</ref> Since 2010, he has represented [[Jamaica national basketball team|Jamaica]] internationally.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://sportsjamaica.com/read_article.php?id=18463|title=Jamaica's Hibbert working hard to reach the top|first=Gordon|last=Williams|date=January 19, 2011|work=Sports Jamaica|publisher=Jamaica Gleaner|accessdate=August 15, 2011}}</ref>}}\n{{Cnote|d|Kosta Koufos was born and raised in the United States to Greek parents. He has represented [[Greece national basketball team|Greece]] internationally.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.fibaeurope.com/container_frontpage.coid_TwXRRK,lH3IVPkIJJiBau2.articleMode_on.html|title=Greek Star Koufos Keeps Feet On The Ground|first=Daniel|last=Aubrey|date=August 9, 2007|work=FIBA Europe|publisher=FIBA|accessdate=August 15, 2011}}</ref>}}\n{{Cnote|e|Serge Ibaka, who was born in [[Republic of the Congo|Congo]], became a naturalized citizen of Spain in 2011.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://espn.go.com/nba/story/_/id/6804350/serge-ibaka-help-adopted-spain-defend-euros-title|title=Serge Ibaka to boost talented Spain|date=July 26, 2011|work=ESPN.com|accessdate=August 15, 2011}}</ref> He has represented [[Spain national basketball team|Spain]] internationally since 2011.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.fibaeurope.com/coid_0fRrDVPpIgktm,Rny3wba3.articleMode_on.html|title=Pau Show as Spain Down France|date=August 9, 2011|work=FIBA Europe|publisher=FIBA|accessdate=August 15, 2011}}</ref>}}\n{{Cnote|f|Dont\u00e9 Greene was born in [[West Germany]] to American parents. He has represented the United States internationally at youth level.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://sportsillustrated.cnn.com/vault/article/magazine/MAG1106915/index.htm|title=Greener Pastures|date=January 22, 2007|first=Franz|last=Lidz|work=Sports Illustrated|publisher=Time Warner Company|accessdate=October 17, 2010}}</ref>}}\n{{Cnote|g|James Gist was born in Turkey to American parents.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://spor.milliyet.com.tr/adanali-fener-e-dogru/spor/spordetay/28.04.2011/1383409/default.htm |title=Adanal\u0131 Fener\u2019e do\u011fru |language=Turkish |trans-title=Fener to Adana |date=April 28, 2011 |work=Milliyet.com.tr |publisher=Demir\u00f6ren-Karacan |accessdate=September 19, 2011 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110728065415/http://spor.milliyet.com.tr/adanali-fener-e-dogru/spor/spordetay/28.04.2011/1383409/default.htm |archivedate=July 28, 2011 }}</ref>}}\n\n==Notable undrafted players==\nThese players were not selected in the 2008 NBA Draft but have played in the NBA.\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable sortable\"\n|-\n! style=\"width:12%;\"| Player\n! style=\"width:1%;\"| Position\n! style=\"width:12%;\"| Nationality\n! style=\"width:12%;\"| School/club team\n|-\n|{{sortname|Gary|Forbes}}\n|SF\n|{{PAN}}\n|[[UMass Minutemen basketball|UMass]] (Sr.)\n|-\n|{{sortname|Sundiata|Gaines}}\n|PG\n|{{flagu|United States}}\n|[[Georgia Bulldogs men's basketball|Georgia]] (Sr.)\n|-\n|{{sortname|Mickell|Gladness}}\n|C\n|{{flagu|United States}}\n|[[Alabama A&M Bulldogs basketball|Alabama A&M]] (Sr.)\n|-\n|{{sortname|Steven|Hill|Steven Hill (basketball)}}\n|PF\n|{{flagu|United States}}\n|[[Arkansas Razorbacks men's basketball|Arkansas]] (Sr.)\n|-\n|{{sortname|Othello|Hunter}}\n|F\n|{{flagu|United States}}\n|[[Ohio State 